r-10432458/', 'content': \"All Dhurandhar box office records: Ranveer Singh film beats Animal to become 10th highest grossing film in India, breaks Jawan, Pushpa 2, Chhaava records | Bollywood News - The Indian Express skip to content Skip To Content by Subscribe Sign In Bollywood Hollywood Videos Television Tamil Telugu Malayalam Regional Web series Movie Review Advertisement News Entertainment Bollywood All Dhurandhar box office records: Ranveer Singh film beats Animal to become 10th highest grossing film in India, breaks Jawan, Pushpa 2, Chhaava records All Dhurandhar box office records: Ranveer Singh film beats Animal to become 10th highest grossing film in India, breaks Jawan, Pushpa 2, Chhaava records Aditya Dhar's period spy thriller Dhurandhar, starring Ranveer Singh, has beaten Ranbir Kapoor's Animal to become the 10th highest grosser in India and surpassed Shah Rukh Khan's Jawan to become the fastest Hindi film to cross the Rs 500 crore mark at the domestic box office. By: Entertainment Desk Mumbai | December 22, 2025 10:23 AM IST 5 min read Whatsapp twitter Facebook Reddit PRINT Ranveer Singh's Dhurandhar is the 10th highest grossing film at the Indian box office. Aditya Dhars period spy thriller Dhurandhar , starring Ranveer Singh in the lead role, continues to dismantle box office records even in its third weekend. The film has now become the 10th highest grossing movie at the Indian box office, dethroning Sandeep Reddy Vangas 2023 family crime drama Animal, headlined by Ranbir Kapoor. 10th highest grosser in India On Sunday, Dhurandhar added another Rs 38.50 crore to its domestic box office collection. Its total earnings in India thus reached Rs 555.75 crore. This leap allowed it to surpass Animal, which previously held the 10th highest grosser position at Rs 553.87 crore. Vanga was all praise for Dhars film as the two exchanged words of appreciation on X even as the latters film dethroned the former. The next target for Dhurandhar is Amar Kaushiks horror comedy Stree 2, starring Rajkummar Rao, which earned Rs 597.99 crore to become the highest grossing Hindi film till last year, as per Sacnilk. Given the current trajectory, Ranveers film is likely to topple Raos movie to become the ninth highest grossing film in India sometime this week. The Rs 600 crore club kicks off from the eighth position in the list of the top 10 highest grossers at the Indian box office. Standing firmly at #8 is Laxman Utekars period action drama Chhaava, starring Vicky Kaushal, which amassed Rs 601.54 crore net this year. It beat Stree, also produced by Dinesh Vijans Maddock Films, to become the highest grossing Hindi film in India. Thus, the top 7 placeholders are pan-India films that released simultaneously in multiple languages. At #7 is another 2025 release Rishab Shettys Kannada period action epic Kantara: Chapter 1, also headlined by him, at Rs 622.43 crore. This makes Dhurandhar the third Indian film this year to make it to the top 10 highest grossers list, following Chhaava and Kantara: Chapter 1. At #6 is Atlees 2023 action thriller Jawan, starring Shah Rukh Khan, which also released in Tamil and Telugu, and earned Rs 640.25 crore across India. The fifth position is held by Nag Ashwins Telugu dystopian sci-fi drama Kalki 2898 AD, starring Prabhas, which amassed Rs 646.31 crore last year. The fourth position is secured by the only Rs 700 crore club member SS Rajamoulis 2022 period action epic RRR, starring Ram Charan and Jr NTR, at Rs 782.20 crore. The third position belongs to the only Rs 800 crore club member Prashanth Neels 2022 action epic KGF: Chapter 2 at Rs 859.70 crore, which also makes it the highest grossing Kannada film in India ever, right above Kantara: Chapter 2. Only the first two placeholders in the list have achieved the feat of surpassing Rs 1,000 crore Rajamoulis 2017 Telugu period action epic Baahubali 2: The Conclusion, starring Prabhas, at Rs 1,030.42 crore and Sukumars 2024 Telugu action thriller Pushpa 2: 